Interface PutCompletionCallback

All Known Implementing Classes:

public interface PutCompletionCallback

Callback called when part of a put request completes.

onEncode

              ClientPutState state,
              com.db4o.ObjectContainer container,

Called when we know the final URI of the state in question. The currentState eventually calls this on the ClientPutter, which relays to the fcp layer, which sends a URIGenerated message.

onMetadata

void onMetadata(Metadata m,
                ClientPutState state,
                com.db4o.ObjectContainer container,
                ClientContext context)
Only called if explicitly asked for, in which case, generally the metadata won't be inserted. Won't be called if there isn't any!

onFetchable

void onFetchable(ClientPutState state,
                 com.db4o.ObjectContainer container)
Called when enough data has been inserted that the file can be retrieved, even if not all data has been inserted yet. Note that this is only supported for splitfiles; if you get onSuccess() first, assume that onFetchable() isn't coming.

Called when the ClientPutState knows that it knows about all the blocks it will need to put.
